result.execSummary:
The defendant Cole C. Vetterkind was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant shall provide a DNA sample to the Taylor County Sheriff's Department.  Defendant shall pay the costs at the rate of $25.00 a month beginning June 1, 2016.
Defendant shall write a letter of apology to the victim and preapproved by the victim witness coordinator.  This has been done.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Cole C. Vetterkind in court.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement put into the record. Victim rights have been complied.  Defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waives right to an attorney.  Plea of guilty.   Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists.  Court finds defendant guilty of Count 1 - DC - domestic and court dismisses and read in count 2.  Statement by Cole Vetterkind.  Court orders court costs; DNA sample and surcharge; letter of apology to victim and preapproved by the victim witness coordinator which has been done.  The costs are to be paid at the rate of $25.00 a month beginning June 1, 2016.  Appeal rights given to defendant.  - rt
Order for Appearance at Settlement Conference; Report to Court on Results of Settlement Conference.

Defendant Cole C. Vetterkind in court.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant waived reading of complaint, charges and penalties.  Court enters plea of not guilty to both charges.  Bond continued.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for March 2, 2016 at 11:00 am.   - rt
Bond Modification Hearing on December 3, 2015 at 10:30 a.m.

Defendant shall not leave the State of Wisconsin without prior notice to and written approval of the court. Defendant shall comply with booking procedures at the Taylor County Sheriff's Department. Defendant shall have no contact with C.M.P.-dob: 01-04-1959.
Initial Appearance on December 29, 2015 at 1:00 p.m.

The Honorable Judge Fox appeared by phone.  Kristi Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant appeared in court in custody. Court found probable cause for the arrest. Court advised DE of possible charges and penalties. Court advised DE of right to attorney.  Notice of right to attorney given to defendant.  State requested a $500.00 cash bond with conditions of: booking, no contact with C.M.P-dob:1-4-59.  Court ordered bond with conditions as requested.  Initial appearance set for December 29, 2015 at 1:00 p.m. -ba
